## Honest caveats

- **Snapshot in time.** Tool versions move. This page is stamped {{RUN_DATE}}.
- **Quarterly re-run pledge.** We re-run in Mar, Jun, Sep, Dec. If a
  competitor pulls ahead between runs, the next publish reflects it. We do
  not delete this file when we are no longer leading; we update it.
- **Judge variance.** LongMemEval uses an LLM judge. Inter-run variance
  is non-zero. Numbers are mean of ≥3 judge passes against the same
  retrievals.
- **Conflicts of interest.** We built nox-mem. The benchmark code is
  open-source. Raw data is published. We invite PRs that improve any
  competitor's configuration.
- **Workload assumptions.** We benchmarked a single-user, 10k-search,
  1k-ingest profile. Heavier or lighter workloads will produce different
  cost and latency shapes.
- **Statistical floor.** With n=100 per latency workload and σ~20ms, 95%
  CI half-width is ≈ ±3.9ms. Latency differences < 8ms are not statistically
  distinguishable.

